itemDescription: Scottish suffragist who established the Orcadian Women's Suffrage Society (fl.1909-1946)

wikipedia_page.main: Mary Anne Baikie (1861 - 1950), was a Scottish suffragist who established the Orcadian Women's Suffrage Society (OWSS) and grew the membership and public interest in the debate, in the Orkney Isles, during the campaigns for Votes for Women.
